fields.description:
Using rapid boards to manage and plan our sprints, the user has a rapid board *Argentina* for which he / she would like to set up a query that contains all issues, which are not part of another sprint in another rapid board. Hence, the following query is being used:

{code}
project in (Maracuja) AND Sprint not in openSprints() ORDER BY Rang
{code}

This query does not return any issues, although there are issues in project *Maracuja* which are not part of an active sprint. However, the following query:

{code}
project in (Maracuja) AND Sprint in openSprints() ORDER BY Rang
{code}

(*Without not*) returns correctly the records which are part of a sprint. Adding *not* should return all the other issues.

The solution was to not use the *openSprints()* function at all but to select issues based on other criteria.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-5446].
  {panel}

If you choose a [viewing mode|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/GH/Using+Planning+Board+Modes] other than 'version' on the planning board and then attempt to edit the version of any issue cards the following error is thrown:
!versionerror.png!

Replicated on Atlassian OnDemand with JIRA 5.1.

I created a sprint with original time and remaining estimate fields empty, logged work to the day before the sprint, and then viewed the sprint report.

Error:
{code}
Exception: Uncaught ReferenceError: pastChangeRows is not defined
Resource: http://wiki.methodware.com:8081/s/en_US2292xv/733/3/486746634889c59348cf27a7f272b979/_/download/contextbatch/js/gh-rapid/batch.js
Line: 1423
Environment
Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/536.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/20.0.1132.47 Safari/536.11
{code}

{panel:title=Workaround| borderStyle=dashed| borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#F7D6C1| bgColor=#FFFFCE} 

This issue has been fixed in GreenHopper 5.10.5, please upgrade to the latest version.

{panel}

Reports from the support team have this exception at plugin start time.

As yet I can see no further investigation into the "log4j" configuration state of play on those systems.

That will be one of the first exercises to do in terms of this bug.

{noformat}
